article.description: — Derrick Butler had 19 points in Central Michigan's 77-62 victory against Kent State on Saturday.
article.headline: Butler scores 19 as Central Michigan knocks off Kent State 77-62
article.linkText: Butler scores 19 as Central Michigan knocks off Kent State 77-62
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. -- — Derrick Butler had 19 points in Central Michigan's 77-62 victory against Kent State on Saturday. Butler shot 7 for 12, including 4 for 5 from beyond the arc for the Chippewas (8-8, 3-1 Mid-American Conference). Brian Taylor scored 17 points and added eight rebounds and six assists. Anthony Pritchard had 11 points and shot 4 for 8, including 1 for 3 from beyond the arc. VonCameron Davis finished with 20 points and two steals for the Golden Flashes (8-8, 1-3). Jalen Sullinger added 17 points and five assists for Kent State. In addition, Chris Payton finished with eight points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
